This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as it deals with the AS-level topology of the Internet. Additionally, the paper uses machine learning techniques to classify ASes, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with the structure and evolution of the Internet, which could place it in the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Furthermore, the paper deals with classification accuracy, which could place it in the sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
